## Conventions

### Commits
- lowercase only, no capital letters anywhere
- concise: one short sentence, under 72 characters
- no emoji, no conventional commit prefixes (`feat:`, `fix:`, etc.)
- no trailers: never add `Co-Authored-By`, `Signed-off-by`, or any trailer lines
- granular: one logical change per commit

### Code Style
- [Naming: camelCase/snake_case/PascalCase and where each is used]
- [Import ordering convention]
- [Error handling patterns]
- [Testing patterns and frameworks]

### Comments & Documentation
- explain why, not what
- CLAUDE.md is the single source of truth for project context
- do not create unnecessary .md files or READMEs unless requested

### Diagrams
- ASCII diagrams for non-trivial data flows, state machines, and dependency graphs
- Place in code comments near the code they describe
- Update diagrams when modifying code they describe â€” stale diagrams are worse than none

### Error Handling
- Name specific exceptions/error types, never catch generic "Error"
- Every rescued error must: retry with backoff, degrade gracefully, or re-raise with context
- "Swallow and continue" is almost never acceptable

## Agent & Skill Routing

When the user's intent matches a pattern below, use the specified agents and skills automatically. Do NOT wait for a slash command â€” route based on what the user is asking for.

### Planning & Scoping
- "plan", "design", "architect", "how should we build" â†’ invoke `superpowers:writing-plans` skill, then dispatch `feature-dev:code-architect` + ECC `architect` agents
- "should we even", "is this worth", "scope", "challenge this", "do we need" â†’ invoke `superpowers:brainstorming` skill, dispatch ECC `planner` agent
- "what could go wrong", "devil's advocate", "risks", "what if this breaks" â†’ dispatch `pr-review-toolkit:silent-failure-hunter` + ECC `security-reviewer` agents in parallel

### Code Review & Quality
- "review", "look over", "check this", "is this good" â†’ dispatch in parallel: `pr-review-toolkit:code-reviewer`, `pr-review-toolkit:silent-failure-hunter`, `pr-review-toolkit:comment-analyzer`, ECC `code-reviewer`
- "review the PR", "PR review", "check the pull request" â†’ invoke `pr-review-toolkit:review-pr` skill (runs 6 parallel agents)
- "security", "vulnerabilities", "audit", "is this secure" â†’ dispatch ECC `security-reviewer` + `pr-review-toolkit:silent-failure-hunter` agents in parallel
- "test coverage", "are tests enough", "missing tests" â†’ dispatch `pr-review-toolkit:pr-test-analyzer` agent
- "types", "type design", "type safety" â†’ dispatch `pr-review-toolkit:type-design-analyzer` agent
- "database", "queries", "schema", "migration" â†’ dispatch ECC `database-reviewer` agent

### Building & Fixing
- "build is broken", "build errors", "won't compile", "fix the build" â†’ dispatch ECC `build-error-resolver` agent (or language-specific: `cpp-build-resolver`, `go-build-resolver`, `java-build-resolver`, `rust-build-resolver`)
- "TDD", "test first", "write tests then code" â†’ invoke `superpowers:test-driven-development` skill, dispatch ECC `tdd-guide` agent
- "bug", "broken", "not working", "failing" â†’ invoke `superpowers:systematic-debugging` skill
- "refactor", "clean up", "dead code", "unused" â†’ dispatch `code-simplifier:code-simplifier` + ECC `refactor-cleaner` agents
- "e2e", "end to end", "integration test" â†’ dispatch ECC `e2e-runner` agent

### Shipping
- "commit", "push", "PR", "ship it", "merge" â†’ invoke `superpowers:verification-before-completion` skill first, then commit
- "verify", "check everything", "ready to ship?" â†’ run build â†’ types â†’ lint â†’ tests â†’ console audit in sequence

### Design & Frontend
- "design system", "colors", "typography", "visual style" â†’ invoke `frontend-design:frontend-design` skill
- "looks wrong", "visual bug", "design review", "UI review" â†’ use Playwright for screenshots, check against DESIGN.md
- "QA", "test the site", "check the pages", "browser test" â†’ use Playwright for systematic page-by-page testing

### Understanding & Exploring
- "explain", "how does this work", "walk me through" â†’ dispatch `feature-dev:code-explorer` agent
- "find", "where is", "search for" â†’ dispatch Explore agent
- "docs", "update documentation" â†’ dispatch ECC `doc-updater` agent

### Research & Experimentation
- "experiment", "try different approaches", "optimize", "iterate", "research" â†’ use experiment loop: modify â†’ run â†’ measure â†’ keep/discard â†’ repeat. Track results in a table. Always establish a baseline first.
- "benchmark", "compare approaches", "which is faster" â†’ run each variant, measure, record in results table, keep the winner

### Session Management
- "what did we learn", "capture this", "remember this" â†’ extract patterns into CLAUDE.md or memory system
- "side question", "quick question", "unrelated but" â†’ pause main task, answer briefly, resume with context summary
- "checkpoint", "save progress", "snapshot" â†’ commit current state with checkpoint prefix

### Language-Specific Review
ECC provides language-specific reviewers that activate automatically based on file types:
- Python files â†’ ECC `python-reviewer`
- Go files â†’ ECC `go-reviewer`
- Rust files â†’ ECC `rust-reviewer`
- C++ files â†’ ECC `cpp-reviewer`
- Java files â†’ ECC `java-reviewer`
- Kotlin files â†’ ECC `kotlin-reviewer`

